        France‚Äôs Ukraine peace discussion </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
     Summary: Putin and Macron engaged in their first conversation since the war in Ukraine. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      French President Emmanuel Macron held a two-hour conversation with Russian President Vladimir Putin. This was their first direct conversation since 2022. Macron reaffirmed France's support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity. He urged Putin to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-jul-25-spotlight-h2-4-agree-to-a-ceasefire" target="_blank">agree to a ceasefire</a> and resume talks for a lasting resolution. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The √âlys√©e presidential palace remarks that this move is a push for peace and de-escalation. However, the Kremlin blamed Western policy for the conflict. Putin insists that any peace agreement must be "<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-long-term" target="_blank">long-term</a>," suggesting ongoing Russian demands for security assurance and possibly the recognition of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-territorial-claims" target="_blank">territorial assertions</a>.
       </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       The leaders discussed Iran‚Äôs nuclear program. They expressed support for a diplomatic resolution and affirmed Tehran's <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-jul-25-spotlight-h2-7-right-to-pursue" target="_blank">right to pursue</a> peaceful nuclear development per international rules. Although the conversation produced no major outcomes, it was a cautious step toward dialogue.</p>
